7:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Feature Analysis"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Both DeepSeek and Microsoft Copilot share a solid foundation of core features including Web Search, File Upload, Code Execution, Multilingual. Where DeepSeek pulls ahead is with exclusive access to Api Access, which can be a deciding factor for teams that rely on this capability. On the other hand, Microsoft Copilot uniquely offers Image Generation and Voice Input and Plugins and Memory and Citations, giving it an edge for users who prioritize these areas. \n\nLooking at user ratings, DeepSeek holds an overall score of 8/10 and an ease of use score of 8/10, while Microsoft Copilot scores 7/10 overall and 8/10 for ease of use. These ratings reflect real user experiences and can indicate differences in usability, support quality, and overall satisfaction."}]]}]
8:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Pricing Breakdown"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"When it comes to pricing, both DeepSeek and Microsoft Copilot offer flexible pricing models. Both platforms offer free plans, which is great for testing before committing. DeepSeek's free tier and Microsoft Copilot's free tier each have their own limitations, so it is worth evaluating both to see which free offering better matches your initial needs."}]]}]
