b:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. DeepSeek is best suited for coding, math, reasoning, technical tasks, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Microsoft Copilot, meanwhile, shines for Office 365 users, enterprise, Windows users, productivity, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2023, DeepSeek describes itself as \"Chinese AI chatbot excelling at coding and mathematical reasoning.\" Microsoft Copilot, established in 2023, positions itself as \"Microsoft's AI assistant integrated across Office 365 and Windows.\" Both platforms have been in the market for a similar duration, giving each ample time to refine their offerings and build a loyal user base."}]]}]
c:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **DeepSeek** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to higher user ratings (8.0 vs 7.0), availability of a free plan. However, this does not mean Microsoft Copilot is a poor choice — far from it. Microsoft Copilot excels in its own right, particularly for Office 365 users and enterprise.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value exceptional coding and math capabilities, go with DeepSeek. If deep microsoft 365 integration matters more to you, Microsoft Copilot is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
